HEADWORD: Legalist
<hw>Le"gal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who practices or advocates
strict conformity to law; in theology, one who holds to the law of
works. See <er>Legal</er>, 2 <sd>(a)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

